Cross-Corpus Findings

One of the clearest patterns to emerge is that Oregon's 2010 performance audits focused predominantly on organizational capability rather than policy direction.

Across agencies, the recommendations consistently emphasized:

stronger governance,
clearer accountability,
improved internal controls,
better information management,
technology modernization,
standardized procedures,
stronger performance measurement.

This suggests the Audits Division's emphasis in 2010 was on improving how government functions, not redefining government programs.
